I want to create an (internal) "portal" web software/platform for a website of an organisation (in this case a non-profit, church/religious organisation - but the final project must not be limited to this and be flexible for use an all kinds of organisations, of all sizes).

The name will be "WebMS Intra" ('Intra' indicating intended for Intranet/internal use)

========================
*TECH STACK and specific instructions*
========================
Please use the following technologies for development of the entire 'Portal' project
* PHP (minimum PHP 8.5 (but with backward compatibility to to PHP 8.4)
	* PHP code should
		* Use PHP Predefined Constants wherever possible to aid with host platform neutrality (ie, use DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR instead of '/' in paths)
		* Full notation for code blocks such as (but not limited to) IF statements, no shortened notation
		* be indented appropriately with detailed inline comments/annotations to assith with code readibility, understanding, debugging and future learning/maintenance of code (where applicable include reference links to documentation to help explain understand the concept)
		* Minimise code duplication but grouping shared code and reusing them via PHP REQUIRE, REQUIRE_ONCE, INCLUDE & INCLUDE_ONCE
		
		  appropriate checks and error handling for REQUIRED and INCLUDED components should be done to avoid errors should files not exist/not be retrievable
		* provide switches  to enable detailed PHP error visiblity by use of a URL Param such as &debug=true (for dev purposes only)
		* log PHP errors/notifictions/warnings (including severity, PHP error code, PHP Error title, error detail, backtrace) to a table in the backend database along with any other errors from components and requested page URL and request headers to assist with debugging/trouble shooting
* MySQL Backend Database
	* Interactions between PHP & MySQL/MariaDB via MySQLi only
	* Use Prepared Statements for all SQL run in PHP
	* Backend database to be used for ALL settings and config as well as records pertaining to the portal and its individual sub-apps
	* Settings should also be stored in the database, including credentials (keys, secrets etc) for third-party services/libraries (like MS365 etc)
	* any confidential secrets/keys (labelled as "isSensitive") must be cryptographically encrypted before entry into the database to ensure data security. Encryption of these confidential info should also use SALT methodology for added security, to current industry standard levels. When retrieving these fields, they should also be decrypted for use.
	* Pre-existing database structure (with some data) is included further down this outline
	
		We are however happy for this structure to be modified as seen fit to improve functionality, flexibility, performance and/or security
* HTML5
	* Must be fully HTML5 compliant, and using modern HTML5 elements
	* Must be fully responsive, and useable on a range of devices, display aspect ratios and display sizes (Hi Res PCs/TV, regular PCs/TV, Tablets, Phones etc)
		* As <table> tags and the like dont work well in a modern responsive web era, please dont use them
* For bot projection of form submission (support for both, with definable order of preference, but the service used depends on provision of required API Keys/secrets)
	* CloudFlare Turnstile
	* ReCapture
* Microsoft 365
	* Used for sending emails using from a Shared Microsoft 365 mailbox (Send As)
	* used for user login, especially for staff/admins/global admins/devs etc
* Google Workspace (future use, but functionality built now)
	* Used for sending emails using from a Shared Microsoft 365 mailbox (SendAs)
	* used for user login, especially for staff/admins/global admins/devs etc
* Support for future implementation/integration of SIGNula (https://github.com/MWBMPartners/SIGNula.id) via its API
	

========================	
*FILE & DATA STRUCTURE*
========================

------------------------	
*Server Files*
------------------------
The Portal will be (in this case) hosted at portal.millrdsdacambridge.uk. the actual Portal files will be hosted on the same webserver as the main application (millrdsdacambridge.uk). BRIEF/HIGH-LEVEL server structure is given below:

<server>
├── _auth_keys/                 	← Site/Server-Wide 🔐 MS365 / DB creds / reCapture / Cloudflare Turnstile & other API Keys (outside web root)
│   ├── auth_creds.php				← Stored securely (not accessible via web)
├── _includes/                  	← Stores Site/Server-wide shared 'includes' that are not directly publically accessible
├── _functions/                		← Stores Site/Server-wide shared 'functions' (PHP or other) that used via php include/require and are not directly publically accessible
├── _libraries/                 	← Stores Site/Server-wide shared 'libraries' (dompdf, Parsedown etc)
├── _uploads/                 		← Stores Site/Server-wide 'uploads' that are not directly publically accessible
├── _backups/                 		← Stores Site/Server-wide 'backups' that are not directly publically accessible
├── millrdsdacambridge.uk/			← Main Website 
│   ├── _auth_keys/                 ← Main Website specific DB creds (outside web root) IF different from side wide
│   │   ├── auth_creds.php          ← Stored securely (not accessible via web)
│   ├── _includes/                  ← Main website specific shared 'includes' that are not directly publically accessible
│   ├── _functions/                 ← Main website specific shared 'functions' (PHP or other) that used via php include/require and are not directly publically accessible
│   ├── _libraries/                 ← Main website specific shared 'libraries' (dompdf, Parsedown etc)
│   ├── _uploads/                 	← Main website specific 'uploads' that are not directly publically accessible
│   ├── _backups/                 	← Main website specific 'backups' that are not directly publically accessible
│   ├── private_html/               ← Main Website public web root
│   ├── public_html/                ← Main Website public web root
│   ├── public_html_dev/			← Main Website Development web root
│   ├── public_html_landing/		← Main Website landing web root
│   ├── public_html_redir/			← Main Website redirection web root
├── portal.millrdsdacambridge.uk/	← Portal (THIS PROJECT, DONT GENERATE ANYTHING FOR OTHER DIRECTORIES, THEYRE JUST PROVIDED FOR SERVER FOLDER STRUCTURE PURPOSES)
│   ├── web/                 		← All Files to be uploaded to server for web-hosting
│   │   ├── _auth_keys/             ← Portal specific DB creds (outside web root) IF different from side wide (not accessible via web)
