========================	
*SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS*
========================

------------------------	
*Overall*
------------------------
* While this will be hosted on Dreamhost shared hosting initially, please include flexibility for hosting on other PHP/MySQL supporting platforms, as such please use PHP constants and predefined constants (such as dirname(), __FILE__, etc for folder defining) wherever possible for platform neutrality/flexibility.
* Given the project will (at least) initially be hosted on Dreamhost's Shared Hosting platform, access to CLI is not possible, as such access to tools like Composer cannot be relied upon. This means any third-party libraries that need to be installed/self-hosted (and cant just be used via referencing CDNs) need to be specifically called out and hosted on local server, often installed/uploaded manually.



------------------------	
*'Mini' Apps within the Portal*
------------------------
The portal will contain various "apps", the first of which is planned for claimants to submit expense claims (app name "Expenses", hosted on the server under '/portal.millrdsdacambridge.uk/public_html/expenses')
Apps should
	* written in such as way so that they support being used as a Web App where beneficial and feasible/practically possible.
	* Provide API endpoints to use/interact with the app
		* Apps should not expose sensitive information, including secrets, keys, passwords, personal email addresses (personal email address will be any email address that does not match with a specified list of suffixes - the bit after the @), or any fields marked in the database as isSensitive
	* Apps that have a need to provide realtime updates/notifications on the website (not via email) may need to utilise websocks or similar technology (compatible with shared hosts such as those provided by Dreamhost)
	* All apps will be assigned a "version number" for internal tracking and have their own changelog
	* Be able to have restricted access, not just for development (beta/alpha) but even "live" version
	* Note this Portal, and its apps are intended for "managing" or recording information. Information from some "apps" may be visible only within the Portal (attendance count), while others (like the "Events" app) could be visible on the main website, but editing only via the portal.


------------------------
	*Calendar of Events* (name: "calendar", possibly suitable as a Web App/PWA)
------------------------
A Calendar events (and "church services" when the Portal is used by Churches) app. Events app provides the following functionlity/workflow:
* List/manage upcoming organisation events, including defining the following info
	* EVENT PARAMETERS
		* Event Name
		* Event Series Name (if its specific scheduled date/event is part of a series) - with series being linkable
		* Event Date & Time (with timezone specified)
		* event end time (with timzeone specified)
		* Event recurrence
			* is event recurring (therefore, it becomes a "Series" which itself can be part of another Series (ie nested Series)
				
				Possible Recurring frequency options:
					* Weekly (Day of the week)
					* Weekdays (Monday-Friday)[Week days could also be defineable for non-western cultures that are traditionally Mon-Fri]
					* Every Weekend Day (Sat-Sun) [Weekend days could also be defineable for cultures that do not follow "western country norms/traditions]
					* Evert nth Day (Sun-Sat) of xth Month (ie every 2nd Monday of the month, or Every 3rd Tuesday, every 3rd Month)
					* Every nth Date of xth Month (ie 2nd of every month, or Every 15th of every 3rd Month)
					* Every nth Day (Sun-Sat) of the Quarter (where quarter is Q1=Jan-Mar; Q2=Apr-Jun; Q3=Jul-Sep; Q4=Oct-Dec)
					* Every nth Date of every xth Year (ie every 24 of March, Every 2nd Year)
					
				Each Event series with recurrence can have individual events that fall outside of the recurrence frequency, but must still be linked.
		* Event Host Org - Organisation hosting/putting on the event)
		* Event Partner Org - Any additional organisations that are involved 'partnersing' with the Host Org to put on the event
		* Event Location
			* Physical Address
			* Web Address
			* Geo-Corodinates
			* What3Words
			* Phone Number
			* contact Email
		
			In the case of a series of events, any individual event part of a series can also be held at a different physical location to the rest of the series
		* Event Theme (multiple themes allowed)
		* Event Type (list of types, that can be added to by admin) - including sub-types
		* Event Category (list of types, that can be added to by admin) - including sub-categories
		* Event Host Person - Person leading the event/main host (could be a special guest)
		* event Other Host People
		* Hero Image (SVG, PNG, JPG or any combination of these)
		* Poster Image (SVG, PNG, JPG, PDF or any combination of these)
		* Profile Picture Image (SVG, PNG, JPG or any combination of these)
		* Event Materials (downloadable documents such as "notes", PDF, Word, PowerPoint, Keynote, Video, Audio or any combination of these)
		* Event Links
			Links relating to the event. Can include anything, including social media pages, booking/rsvp pages etc
		
* Events should be able to be listed/embedable as follows
	* Direct link to single scheduled event
	* Direct link to Series of events, listing each item in the series in a fully responsive table
	* Direct link to All events, in a given day/week/month/year, displayed as:
		* Table
		* Calendar display
		* Year-planner style layout with multiple events per day, each highlighted according to category (lowest level category in case of sub/nested-categories)
		
		Click on each of these items goes to the scheduled event itself.
	* List ALL events in a fully responsive table (regardless of timeframe, but with toggles to show only future events vs also including past and events currently taking place)
	* Add/Subscribe to any event to your local Calendar (Google Calendar, Outlook Calendar, Email client calendar), including support for dynamic updating of local calendar listing if event date/time changes. Include support for linked/series events
	
* Future integration with another upcoming MWBM Partners Ltd Events "platform"


